Race.SpecificTitle: South Bossier Parish Fire District No. 2 -- 3.50 Mills - BOC - 15 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
South Bossier Parish Fire District No. 2 Proposition
(Millage)
Race.FullText: Shall South Bossier Parish Fire District No. 2 of the Parish of Bossier, State of Louisiana (the "District"), be authorized to levy and collect a special tax of three and fifty hundredths (3.50) mills on all property subject to taxation in the District (an estimated $398,400 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of fifteen (15) years, beginning with the year 2023 and ending with the year 2037, for the purpose of acquiring, constructing, improving, maintaining or operating fire protection and emergency medical service facilities, vehicles and equipment, including both movable and immovable property, that are to be used to provide fire protection and medical service in the District, including paying the cost of obtaining water for fire protection purposes and salaries of firemen, and all purposes incidental thereto?
